name: iuya Aeyu
review_text:
Location are awesome  dil khush hua ayse location aake

The Elephant Falls are a two-tier waterfall in Shillong, Meghalaya, India.The mountain stream descends through two successive falls set in dells of fern-covered rocks.

The original Khasi name for the falls is Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, which translates to the three-step waterfall.This name is still used locally. However, the modern name is explained by a signboard near the waterfall.The name originated in the British era when the Englishmen spotted a giant rock that looked like an elephant near the fall. This rock was destroyed in the 1897 due to an earthquake.

name: Akash Joseph
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination in Shillong for nature lovers and those seeking a serene escape. The cascading waterfalls, surrounded by lush greenery, create a breathtakingly picturesque setting. The falls are divided into three levels, and a well-maintained staircase allows visitors to explore each tier comfortably.

The sound of the water rushing over the rocks is soothing, and the clean, fresh air adds to the experience. There are plenty of photo opportunities at every level, making it a paradise for photography enthusiasts.

The site is well-managed, with parking facilities, restrooms, and a few shops nearby selling souvenirs and refreshments. The entry fee is nominal, and the path is safe, though a bit steep in parts, so comfortable footwear is recommended.

Overall, Elephant Falls is a gem in Meghalaya that showcases the region's natural beauty and charm. It's perfect for a short visit and offers a tranquil break from the hustle and bustle of daily life. Highly recommended for all visitors to Shillong!

name: Bishal Sah
review_text:
We visited Elephant Falls in the morning when there were very few people around. The place is very neat and clean with several souvenir shops outside the gate which sell a variety of items to take home. The first falls is just a small climb and can be viewed by everyone. The second falls are a few more steps down and more like a hidden fall. The third and last falls requires one to climb down steeper steps and is where the falls end. It is a bit difficult to climb up but still comparatively easier than other falls in the region. There was lot of water in the falls and is a must visit place if you are in Shillong.

To avoid tourist visit in the morning

name: Monimugdha Bhuyan
review_text: Elephant Falls is one of the most popular and picturesque waterfalls in Meghalaya, located about 12 km from the city of Shillong. Named by the British after a nearby rock that resembled an elephant (which was later destroyed in an earthquake), the falls are known locally as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, meaning The Three Step Waterfalls, because it flows down in three distinct cascades. Surrounded by lush greenery and dense forests, the waterfall offers a serene and refreshing escape from the city. The first cascade is broad and relatively gentle, while the second is narrower and flows through jagged rocks, and the final tier plunges dramatically into a shallow pool below. A well-maintained trail with steps and viewing platforms allows visitors to easily explore each tier, making the falls both accessible and enjoyable. The best time to visit is during or just after the monsoon season (June to September), when the falls are at their fullest, though the cool climate of Shillong makes it a pleasant destination year-round. With its scenic beauty and close proximity to the city, Elephant Falls is a must-visit spot for tourists, nature lovers, and photographers exploring the landscapes of Meghalaya. Entry fees Rs. 100 per person.

name: Nil Akash
review_text:
Elephant falls is a three step waterfall.It is situated at the outskirts of the main city of Shillong in the East khashi hill District,Upper Shillong. It is nearly 12 km away from the Shilling center point. This includes Shillong local sightseeing.Entry ticket fare is Rs-100.The first fall of Elephant Falls is an example of a Horsetail-waterfall. The first fall is very broad and is hidden among trees. The second fall however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes into view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.

name: Kiron Moni Ahmed
review_text:
Elephant Falls, Meghalaya: A Natural Gem Worth Visiting

Elephant Falls in Meghalaya is an absolute must-visit for nature lovers. Located just a short drive from Shillong, this majestic three-tiered waterfall is nestled amidst lush greenery, creating a peaceful and scenic ambiance. Each level of the falls offers a unique perspective, with the final tier being the most impressive as the water cascades down the rocks with force and grace.

What truly sets Elephant Falls apart is the serenity of the area. Despite being a popular tourist spot, the surroundings feel calm and relatively untouched. The path leading to the falls is well-maintained, making it easy for visitors of all ages to navigate. There are plenty of spots to sit and take in the breathtaking view, and the cool mist from the waterfall is refreshing, especially on a warm day.

The name Elephant Falls comes from a rock formation that once resembled an elephant but was unfortunately destroyed by an earthquake. However, the falls still retain their charm and allure. I highly recommend visiting in the early morning or late afternoon when the light enhances the natural beauty.

Overall, Elephant Falls offers an unforgettable experience, blending natural beauty, tranquility, and a sense of adventure. Perfect for photography enthusiasts, couples, or families looking to reconnect with nature. Dont forget to stop by the small market at the entrance for some local souvenirs.

name: Debasish Debnath
review_text:
The city of ice of the state of cloud ,full of tourist attraction in North Eastern region Shillong is the queen of beauty and present environment also.
Our world famous poet Rabindranath Tagore many times came here. Many eminent personalies often come here to see its charms .
But last month while I visited found new changes there.
In this month of September the city, which would be under 12 degree temperature minimum nowadays increased to 21 degree or above .
Similarly max which was 23 , now it become 32 or above.
In shiling previously no where there were any option of celling Fan option. But now Fans are seen many places and company Distributors of celling Fan already open their business in the city.
Local fruits are not available like that time but fruit sellers find more profit by transporting / importing fruit from kashmir.
Great changes are observed in Shilong.
Global warming plays an important role regarding such changes.
The issues regarding local youths fresh and spontaneous lifestyle and soft personality was remaining same where as most important Blessing of Megalaya as I think is Natural Stone and the Natiinal Highway from Shillong to Guwahati.
These two may be the  Blessings of Meghalaya .
Because suppose to o construction boundary wall other than that state we need 2000 nos Brick @ Rs 20.00/ each @Total Rs 40000 along with Transportaton cost of Rs 3000, which in total cones around Rs. 43000.00

name: Manasa shetty
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a popular tourist spot located in Shillong, known for its three-tiered waterfall that offers a stunning natural view. To visit, you need to purchase an entrance ticket, which costs around 100 rupees. There is a parking area available free of charge, where you can leave your vehicle. At the entrance, you also have the opportunity to wear the traditional Khasi dress, a unique experience reflecting the local culture.

The first waterfall greets you with its beauty, and as you continue, youll come across the second and third waterfalls, connected by a scenic bridge. After exploring the waterfalls, you can relax in a nearby park, making it a complete experience. However, one downside is that visitors are charged an additional ticket fee at one point within the area, which some find disappointing.

Its important to note that there are no food options available inside the waterfall area, so its best to grab a meal outside before your visit. Restrooms are available on-site for convenience. Overall, Elephant Falls is a beautiful and refreshing destination that offers a memorable experience for nature lovers.

name: Hemant Meher
review_text:
Elephant Waterfall in Shillong, Meghalaya, is a breathtaking natural wonder that captivates with its serene beauty and cascading waters. Nestled amidst lush greenery, this three-tiered waterfall offers a mesmerizing view, with each layer presenting a unique charm. The gentle roar of the water and the misty spray create a tranquil ambiance, perfect for nature lovers and photographers alike. The descent to the waterfall is well-maintained, with steps leading to the base for an up-close experience. The surrounding area is rich in flora, enhancing the scenic beauty. Visiting Elephant Waterfall is like stepping into a tranquil paradise, making it a must-see destination for anyone exploring Shillong.

Elephant Falls in Shillong is a magnificent tourist destination that offers an unforgettable experience. The cascading waterfalls, surrounded by lush greenery, create a serene and picturesque setting that captivates every visitor. The beauty of this place is truly mesmerizing and a perfect spot for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts.
What adds to the allure of Elephant Falls is the fact that our Prime Minister of India also visited this site to promote tourism, recognizing its potential to attract tourists from all over the world. The well-maintained pathways and viewing points allow visitors to appreciate the falls from various angles, enhancing the overall experience.

A visit to Elephant Falls is a must for anyone exploring Shillong, offering a serene escape into natures splendor.

name: DEBANJAN PATHAK VLOGS
review_text:
Elephant Falls is an amazing place to visit in Shillong. This falls is known as three step falls to local people. This falls falls from top to bottom in three steps. If you go during the rainy season, you will find this waterfall more lively. The entry fee here is Rs.100/- per person. You can also take pictures here in Meghalaya traditional dress. There is no phone network near this falls. There was a big stone like an elephant near this falls, which the British called this fall Elephant Falls, after the 1897 earthquake, the stone was destroyed.

name: Anupol Choudhury
review_text:
I recently visited Elephant Falls in Meghalaya and absolutely loved the experience, especially the first fall. The seating arrangement near the first fall is excellent, providing a comfortable spot to sit and enjoy the beautiful view. Its easily accessible and perfect for elders who might want to avoid the more strenuous paths.

However, I wouldnt recommend going to the other falls if you have mobility issues, as the paths can be quite steep and challenging. The first fall is stunning and offers a great experience on its own, making it a must-visit if youre in the area. Overall, Elephant Falls is a beautiful spot to enjoy nature and relax.

name: Zeeshan Khursheed
review_text:
Elephant Falls in Shillong is an absolute gem! Nestled in the heart of Meghalaya, this three-tiered waterfall is a visual and auditory delight. Each tier has its own unique charm, and the cascades create a mesmerizing spectacle. The first fall is broad and gentle, the second is more rugged and dramatic, and the third tier is the most impressive, with water gushing down with incredible force.

The path to the falls is well-maintained, and there are plenty of viewpoints where you can stop to take in the beauty and snap some amazing photos. The lush greenery surrounding the falls adds to the serene atmosphere, making it a perfect spot for nature lovers.

What I particularly appreciated was the ease of access. The steps are manageable, even for those who might not be in peak physical condition, and there are resting spots along the way. Theres also a small souvenir shop near the entrance where you can pick up some local crafts.

Parking is convenient, and the area is clean and well-kept. The best time to visit is during the monsoon season when the falls are at their most powerful and the surroundings are lush and vibrant.

Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit when in Shillong. Whether youre a solo traveler, a couple, or with family, the experience is refreshing and rejuvenating. Highly recommended!

name: Anuj Gupta (Raj)
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a picturesque waterfall located near Shillong, the capital city of Meghalaya, India. It is one of the most popular tourist attractions in the region, known for its natural beauty and serene environment. Here are some key details about Elephant Falls.

Key Features of Elephant Falls

1. **Name and Origin**:
- The name Elephant Falls was given by British colonists because a rock at the base of the falls resembled an elephant. Unfortunately, this rock was destroyed in an earthquake in 1897.
- Locally, the falls are known as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, which means The Three Step Waterfalls in the Khasi language, referring to the three distinct sections of the falls.

2. **Structure and Appearance**:
- The waterfall consists of three segments, each falling from a different height, creating a stunning visual effect.
- The first part of the fall is broad and plunges into a small pool, the second part is hidden between the dense vegetation and rock structures, and the third part is the most visible and awe-inspiring as it cascades down the rocks.

3. **Scenic Beauty**:
- The surrounding area is lush with greenery, with dense forests and various plant species, contributing to the tranquil and picturesque setting.
- The falls are particularly impressive during the monsoon season when the water flow is at its peak.

4. **Tourist Facilities**:
- There are well-maintained footpaths and steps leading to different viewing points, allowing visitors to experience the falls from various angles.
- The site is equipped with rest areas, benches, and viewing platforms to enhance the visitor experience.

5. **Accessibility**:
- Elephant Falls is located approximately 12 kilometers from Shillong, making it easily accessible by road. Visitors can hire taxis, take buses, or drive to the site.
- The falls are open throughout the year, but the best time to visit is during the post-monsoon season (September to November) when the water flow is optimal and the surroundings are lush green.

6. **Nearby Attractions**:
- Visitors often combine their trip to Elephant Falls with visits to other nearby attractions such as Shillong Peak, Ward's Lake, and the Don Bosco Museum.

### Visiting Information

- **Timings**: The falls are typically open to visitors from early morning to late afternoon. It is advisable to check the exact timings before planning a visit.
- **Entry Fee**: A nominal entry fee is usually charged for access to the falls, which goes towards the maintenance of the site.
- **Safety**: While the paths and viewing platforms are generally safe, it is important for visitors to wear comfortable shoes and be cautious, especially during the rainy season when the paths can be slippery.

### Conclusion

Elephant Falls in Shillong is a must-visit destination for nature lovers and those seeking a peaceful retreat amidst natural beauty. Its unique three-step structure, lush surroundings, and easy accessibility make it a favorite spot for tourists visiting Meghalaya.

name: Anthony
review_text:
The original Khasi name for the falls is Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, which translates to the three - step waterfall. This name is still used locally. However the modern name is explained by a signboard near the waterfall. The name originated in the British era when the Englishmen spotted a giant rock that looked like an elephant near the fall. This rock was destroyed in 1897 due to an earthquake.
Elephant Falls is situated at the outskirts of the main city of Shillong in the East Khasi Hills District, Upper Shillong. It is almost 12 km away from the Shillong city center.

review_text:
Elephant Falls in Shillong, Meghalaya, is a picturesque three-tiered waterfall, named for a rock resembling an elephant that once existed near the falls. It is surrounded by lush greenery, making it a popular spot for nature lovers and photographers. We tried local traditional clothes and the experience was awesome. The best time to visit is during the monsoon season when the falls are at their most impressive, with the water flow at its peak.

name: PRAGATA MUKHERJEE
review_text:
The name originated in the British era when the Englishmen spotted a giant rock that looked like an elephant near the fall. This rock was destroyed in 1897 due to an earthquake.

The falls are surrounded by beautiful green trees and undulating hills that drop from a height of roughly 30 meters.The breathtaking Elephant falls were referred to as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew by the local Khasi people, which means The Three Step Waterfalls, as these falls consist of three mesmerising falls in succession.

A ticket costing 20 INR is required to view the fall with an additional charge of 20 INR for permission to bring the camera. (Variable)

Parking available.

review_text: Elephant Falls, located near Shillong in Meghalaya, is one of the most popular and picturesque waterfalls in the region. Named by the British for an elephant-shaped rock near the falls, which has since disintegrated, the site consists of three distinct cascades, each offering its unique charm. The first fall is broad and hidden among trees, the second is more tamed and shallow, and the third and most spectacular is a fast-flowing drop over sharp rocks. The surrounding lush greenery and well-maintained pathways make for a pleasant and accessible visit. There are viewing platforms and steps that provide close-up views and photo opportunities of the cascading water. The falls are particularly impressive during the monsoon season when they are at their fullest. Elephant Falls provides a serene and refreshing escape, making it a must-visit for nature enthusiasts and tourists exploring the beauty of Meghalaya.

name: Pranab Sharma
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a breathtaking natural wonder. As you stroll through the lush greenery, the sound of cascading water fills the air, creating a serene atmosphere. The falls, named after a rock formation resembling an elephant, offer a mesmerizing sight.
Visitors can get up close to the falls and feel the refreshing spray of water. The surrounding landscape is picturesque, perfect for capturing memorable moments.
However, accessibility might be a challenge for some, as there are stairs to navigate.

Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination when you are in Shillong.

name: abhishek mishra
review_text:
Title: Natures Majesty Unveiled: Exploring Elephant Falls in Shillong

Nestled amidst the lush greenery of Meghalaya, Elephant Falls in Shillong stands as a testament to the breathtaking beauty of the regions natural landscape. Having recently visited this captivating waterfall, I am compelled to share my experience and invite others to discover the awe-inspiring wonders that await at this picturesque destination.

From the moment one sets foot on the well-trodden path leading to Elephant Falls, a sense of anticipation begins to build. The air is alive with the symphony of cascading water and rustling leaves, while the earthy scent of damp moss and ferns fills the senses, creating an atmosphere of enchantment and mystery.

As the trail winds deeper into the heart of the forest, the sound of rushing water grows louder, heralding the approach to the majestic waterfall. And then, suddenly, it reveals itself: Elephant Falls, a magnificent cascade of frothy white water tumbling over moss-covered rocks, framed by verdant foliage and towering trees.

What sets Elephant Falls apart is its sheer grandeur and natural splendor. As the water plunges gracefully into the pool below, it creates a mesmerizing display of power and beauty, captivating the imagination and stirring the soul. Its a scene straight out of a postcard, a testament to the timeless beauty of natures handiwork.

Moreover, Elephant Falls offers more than just visual spectacle; it provides a serene escape from the hustle and bustle of everyday life. Here, amidst the tranquil embrace of the forest, one can immerse oneself in the sights and sounds of nature, finding solace in the rhythmic dance of the waterfall and the gentle rustle of leaves.

For those feeling adventurous, Elephant Falls offers the opportunity to explore its surroundings further, with walking trails leading to hidden viewpoints and secluded alcoves. Each new discovery adds to the sense of wonder and awe, making every step along the journey a memorable experience.

In conclusion, Elephant Falls in Shillong is a true gem that captivates the senses and leaves a lasting impression on the heart. With its majestic beauty, tranquil atmosphere, and sense of natural wonder, it offers the perfect escape for those seeking solace amidst the splendor of the natural world. So, if youre in search of adventure, beauty, and a true connection with nature, look no further than Elephant Falls--you wont be disappointed.

Notes:
1. No choice of bathing here.
2. No rush

name: Raghavendra Peddi
review_text:
Nestled amidst the lush hills surrounding Shillong, Elephant Falls isnt just a scenic wonder, its an experience. Unlike the awe-inspiring remoteness of Nohkalikai Falls, Elephant Falls offers a chance to get up close and personal with its cascading beauty.

The journey itself is delightful. Imagine a gentle walk through verdant foliage, sunlight dappling the path, and the sound of cascading water growing steadily louder. As you arrive, the first tier of the falls unfolds before you - a broad curtain of water gushing down moss-covered rocks. The air is cool and refreshing, carrying a fine mist that dances on your skin.

The true magic lies in exploring further. Unlike Nohkalikais distant grandeur, Elephant Falls allows you to descend (with caution!) along well-maintained steps. Each tier reveals a different character - the first, a powerful cascade, the second, a series of delicate streams, and the final one, the crown jewel. The third tier is the most impressive, with water cascading down a sheer rock face, creating a mesmerizing scene.

The sound of the falls is a symphony in itself. It drowns out the everyday noise, leaving you with a sense of tranquility. Take a moment to sit on a nearby rock, breathe in the fresh air, and let the cascading water wash away your worries.

While not the tallest or most dramatic waterfall, Elephant Falls holds a special charm. Its a place to reconnect with nature, create lasting memories, and capture the beauty on camera (or simply in your minds eye)

name: Rama Kanta Baro
review_text:
Shillong is known for its breathtaking natural beauty and diverse flora. The city is blessed with a wide range of waterfalls, each with its unique charm. Be it the popular Elephant Falls or the serene Bishop Falls, every waterfall in Shillong is a sight to behold. Moreover, the city itself is a paradise for nature lovers. With a healthy climate and an abundance of greenery, its no surprise that visitors are often reluctant to leave.

Apart from being a scenic wonderland, Shillong is also a budget-friendly place to visit. From budget-friendly guesthouses to affordable eateries, the city caters to tourists of all kinds. And if youre someone who loves adventure, Shillong wont disappoint you. The city offers a plethora of adventure sports, from trekking and hiking to water sports and camping.

In summary, Shillong, Meghalaya is a must-visit destination for anyone who loves nature, adventure, and budget-friendly travel. So why not plan a trip to this heaven on earth and explore the wonders of Shillong for yourself?

name: Dr Sangeetha Bhat
review_text:
If you just have a day in Shillong I would advice you to skip this one , since the waterfall is ok ok compared to the others in the state . Also there is a price of 100/- on the ticket for which it is totally not worth. The waterfall is good looking, but nothing mesmerising about it. Rather visit krang shuri or chirapunji. If the intention is to visit sites in Shillong, shillong peak(@ 60/- per person and 200 per cab of 3), laitlum canyon , wards lake and umiam lake are worth the time efforts and money. We missed wards lake as we lost time visiting this place.
There are steps which need to be climbed down. The steps to the first level fall is relatively easy, the second and third falls ,you need to climb down some steeper steps which might be difficult for senior citizens to climb back up . So unless you have 2 days at least on hand , dont bother visiting elephant falls

name: Manas Kumar Saha
review_text:
There are 3 steps in Elephant Falls, Shillong. Due to my physical condition, I could go only upto 1st step, which is only about 60-70 steps.
The tourist amenities are really good, not only at this place, but all over Meghalaya, Cherapunji, everywhere you will find clean toilet with western style toilets, soap dispenser, water availability, and of course, food.
Nice quality food, tea, cold drinks etc, and very large area of parking, where at least 100 vehicles can park.
The scenery at Elephant Falls was good, but, in rainy season with so much water, you will not want to leave the place. Its mesmerizing.
Highly recommended.

name: Gyan Sidar
review_text: Elephant Falls, the Scotland of the East, is located on the outskirts of Shillong. What makes this waterfall different among the series of natural treasures found in Shillong is that the waterfall has three sections that flow in sequence. It is one of the busiest tourist places around, especially if you go there in monsoon. During this season, autumn is in full swing and even the locals cannot stop themselves from getting a glimpse of this mighty autumn. So if this is the time you visit the falls, make sure you know what to expect.

name: Supriya Parab
review_text:
Major tourist attraction of Shillong sight seeing...

It is located 12 km away from Shillong...

A must visit place in Shillong.

It is three layers of water falls...

 The third waterfall which is the best of the three and the biggest...

The third waterfall attracts people towards it due to its thick and milky water body...

You can click numerous pictures at the waterfalls and surroundings...

Time require - 30 to 40 minutes to see the place properly...

you can click some pictures wearing local Khasi attire which is rented at the shop near the Elephant Falls at a very reasonable rates which is Rs. 100 per person....

name: Vijay Reddy Venumuddala
review_text:
A must visit place in Megalaya....The first fall of Elephant Falls is an example of a horsetail-punchbowl waterfall. The first fall is very broad and is hidden among the trees. The second fall however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes to view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.
The sides of the waterfall are flanked by lush greenery and are rich in ferns

name: Vishwa Prasad
review_text:
Nestled amidst the lush greenery and pristine landscapes of Shillong, Meghalaya, Elephant Falls stands as a captivating testament to natures artistry. Renowned for its cascading waters, verdant surroundings, and serene ambiance, this iconic attraction beckons travelers to immerse themselves in its tranquil embrace and marvel at its timeless beauty.

Spectacular Scenery:

The journey to Elephant Falls is as enchanting as the destination itself, winding through verdant forests and rolling hills that offer glimpses of Meghalayas breathtaking natural splendor. As visitors approach the falls, the sound of rushing water grows louder, heightening anticipation for the spectacle that awaits.

Upon arrival, the sight of Elephant Falls is nothing short of mesmerizing. The cascading waters tumble gracefully over rocky ledges, creating a spectacle of mist and spray that dances in the sunlight. Lush green foliage surrounds the falls, framing the scene like a verdant tapestry and enhancing its ethereal beauty. Whether viewed from a distance or up close, the sheer magnificence of Elephant Falls leaves an indelible impression on all who behold it.

Refreshing Climate:

One of the most delightful aspects of visiting Elephant Falls is the refreshing climate that prevails throughout the year. Shillongs temperate weather, characterized by cool breezes and mild temperatures, provides the perfect backdrop for exploring this natural wonder. Even during the summer months, when much of the country swelters in heat, Shillong remains a cool oasis, offering respite from the scorching sun and inviting travelers to bask in its pleasant embrace.

As visitors meander along the trails leading to the falls, they are greeted by the gentle rustle of leaves and the melodious chirping of birds--a symphony of natures harmonies that soothes the soul and rejuvenates the spirit. The crisp, clean air invigorates the senses, imbuing each moment with a sense of vitality and vitality.

Immersive Experience:

Beyond its scenic beauty and favorable climate, Elephant Falls offers visitors the opportunity for an immersive experience that connects them with the natural world on a deeper level. Adventurous souls can venture closer to the falls, feeling the cool mist on their skin and listening to the rhythmic drumming of water against rock. Photographers will find endless inspiration in the play of light and shadow, capturing the falls from various angles to preserve the moment for eternity.

For those seeking moments of solitude and reflection, Elephant Falls provides secluded alcoves and quiet corners where one can commune with nature in solitude. Whether sitting by the waters edge, listening to the gentle babble of the stream, or simply gazing out at the panoramic vistas that stretch to the horizon, visitors cannot help but feel a sense of peace and tranquility wash over them.

Elephant Falls in Shillong offers not only a breathtaking natural spectacle but also a sanctuary for the soul--a place where visitors can escape the hustle and bustle of daily life and reconnect with the rhythms of nature. With its picturesque scenery, favorable climate, and immersive ambiance, it is no wonder that Elephant Falls remains a beloved destination for travelers seeking solace and inspiration amidst the beauty of Meghalayas landscape.

name: God
review_text:
4*. Why? Entry fee is quite high. 200 for a car.

Other than that, fabulous waterfalls. Beautiful.

It can be covered during the Shillong local tour. Keep in mind, do not follow what your hired tour vehicle says of showing you places around Shillong. There aren't much to see IN Shillong. Make them include laitlum canyon in for the same price, or maybe, 10% extra while omitting the places you wouldn't want to visit.

Coming to this waterfalls, it can be seen from another park but no point in going there if you can see it from here, up close and personal. ;)

There aren't too many steps. Couch potatoes and unfit people will tell you there's a lot. Kudos to the fit and regular exercise people.
You'll have to go down and up approximately a 5-7 storey building stairs length. So, less than moderate workout. First you'll reach the First falls. On the way to it, there are areas where you can get your picture taken in a traditional Khasi dress. 150 as of February 2024 for that.

After the first falls, descending starts. That's the main part. Easy to go up or down the stairs. Cement stairs.

The base of the falls, there's a rope which you aren't allowed to cross. No swimming allowed.

Enjoy your descent and ascent. DO NOT DIRTY OR LITTER THE PLACE. Enjoy Meghalaya. Happy trip. :)

name: Aditya Raj
review_text:
Elephant Falls, located near Shillong in the northeastern state of Meghalaya, India, is a stunning natural attraction that captivates visitors with its beauty and tranquility. The falls are named after a rock resembling an elephant near the foot of the waterfall, adding a touch of whimsy to the already enchanting setting.

Upon arriving at Elephant Falls, visitors are greeted by the soothing sound of cascading water as it flows gracefully down multiple tiers, creating a mesmerizing sight. The lush greenery surrounding the falls adds to the natural charm of the area, making it a perfect spot for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts.

The falls are easily accessible via a short walk from the parking area, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in the serene ambiance of the surroundings. The cool mist from the waterfall adds a refreshing touch to the experience, making it a welcome respite from the hustle and bustle of everyday life.

One of the highlights of Elephant Falls is the opportunity to explore the different vantage points that offer unique perspectives of the cascading water. From the base of the falls to the viewing platforms strategically placed along the trail, visitors can admire the beauty of the waterfall from various angles, each offering a different glimpse of its splendor.

The surrounding area also boasts picnic spots and seating areas where visitors can relax and enjoy a leisurely break while taking in the sights and sounds of nature. The tranquil atmosphere of Elephant Falls makes it an ideal destination for those seeking a peaceful retreat amidst the beauty of Meghalayas landscape.

Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination for anyone traveling to Meghalaya, offering a serene and picturesque setting that showcases the natural beauty of the region. Whether youre a nature enthusiast, a photography buff, or simply looking for a peaceful escape, Elephant Falls promises an unforgettable experience that will leave you in awe of its majestic beauty.

name: Paulomi Basu
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a breathtaking three-layered cascade, impeccably maintained, and truly beautiful with no entry ticket.

The journey to the end involves numerous stairs, which might be challenging for older individuals.

At the entry point, there are a couple of shops offering local items, adding a cultural touch to the visit.

Additionally, there are convenient amenities like restaurants and washrooms available nearby, enhancing the overall visitor experience.

In summary, Elephant Falls is a must-visit for nature enthusiasts, offering both natural beauty and accessibility to facilities for a comfortable visit.

name: Md meraj Khan
review_text:
Elephant Falls in Shillong, Meghalaya, is a mesmerizing natural wonder. The cascading water, surrounded by lush greenery, creates a serene atmosphere. The well-maintained pathways offer easy access, allowing visitors to enjoy the scenic beauty effortlessly. However, its advisable to visit during the monsoon for a more spectacular view. Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination for nature enthusiasts seeking tranquility amidst Meghalayas picturesque landscapes.
Visited on
Weekday

Wait time

Reservation recommended

name: Iphence T Jose
review_text:
Elephant Falls is one of the most popular falls in the North-East, situated in the outskirts of Shillong. It is a tourists paradise with three layers of falls. The Britishers named this fall so owing to the presence of an elephant-shaped rock on one side of the fall. However, the stone was destroyed due to an earthquake in 1897. Elephant Waterfalls is a superb place for spending some time in the midst of nature.
The Elephant falls were referred to as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew by the local Khasi people, which means The Three Step Waterfalls, as these falls consist of three mesmerising falls in succession. Elephant Falls is a great stopover destination before one heads for further journeys into Meghalaya. Located 12 km away from the capital city of Shillong.

name: Prashant Dumbre
review_text:
My visit to Elephant Falls was an absolute delight and a highlight of my trip. Tucked away in the lush green landscapes, this natural wonder is a testament to the breathtaking beauty that Mother Nature can create.

The journey to the falls is an adventure in itself, with scenic trails surrounded by dense foliage. Once you reach the falls, the thunderous sound of cascading water and the misty spray in the air create a mesmerizing atmosphere. The sight of the water gracefully flowing down the rocks is nothing short of spectacular.

The well-maintained pathways and viewing platforms make it easy to explore the area and capture the perfect photo. The lush greenery and vibrant flora surrounding Elephant Falls make it a photographers paradise. Dont forget your camera!

I was impressed by the efforts made to preserve the natural environment. There are informative signs about the local flora and fauna, raising awareness about the importance of conservation. Its heartening to see a destination that values its ecological heritage.

For adventure seekers, there are opportunities to venture closer to the falls and feel the invigorating spray of water. However, safety measures are in place, ensuring a thrilling yet secure experience.

Whether youre a nature enthusiast, a photographer, or just someone seeking a peaceful retreat, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination. Its a perfect blend of natural beauty, tranquility, and a sense of awe that stays with you long after you leave. I highly recommend adding Elephant Falls to your itinerary - its a nature lovers paradise!

name: Dr. RM, A Traveller
review_text:
A beautiful waterfall near the main town.
Meghalaya trip is incomplete without a visit to the Elephant Falls, which is located on the outskirts of Shillong. The waterfall results of a mountain stream that rolls over multiple levels, move through the forested slope. The local Khasi name for the Elephant Falls is Kshaid-Lai-Pateng, which refers to the three levels over which the water jumps. The name is rather misleading today-the elephant-shaped rock after which it was named by the British was destroyed in an earthquake more than a hundred years ago.

name: Bhagyashree Nath
review_text:
A Mesmerizing Jewel in Shillongs Crown - Elephant Falls



Elephant Falls in Shillong is nothing short of a natural masterpiece that leaves visitors enchanted and awe-inspired. Nestled amidst the lush landscapes of Meghalaya, this iconic waterfall is a must-visit for anyone exploring the enchanting Northeast of India.

From the moment you set foot in the Elephant Falls Park, you are greeted by the soothing sounds of cascading water and the refreshing scent of nature. The well-maintained pathways and greenery surrounding the area add to the overall charm of the place. As a nature enthusiast, I was thrilled to explore this haven of tranquility.

The journey to the main waterfall is an adventure in itself. The pathway leading to Elephant Falls is lined with vibrant flora, and the gentle murmur of the stream accompanies you as you stroll along. The anticipation builds with every step, and as you turn a corner, the majestic Elephant Falls comes into view.

The first tier of the falls, named Wei Iaplam, is a sight to behold. The water plunges down from a rocky outcrop, creating a mesmerizing display of natural beauty. The sheer force and intensity of the water, coupled with the surrounding greenery, make for a picturesque setting. Its the perfect spot for photographers looking to capture the raw power of nature.

A short trek further upstream leads you to the second tier, Wei Iapoh, which is equally captivating. Here, the water gracefully flows over a series of rocks, creating small pools that reflect the sunlight in a dazzling dance of colors. The serenity of this spot makes it an ideal place for those seeking a peaceful retreat.

What sets Elephant Falls apart is its unique rock formations and the way the water weaves its way through the landscape. The rocks, covered in moss and ferns, add a touch of mystique to the entire setting. Visitors can get up close to feel the cool spray of water on their faces, making the experience immersive and refreshing.

The park authorities have done an excellent job of providing well-maintained viewing platforms and seating areas, allowing visitors to relax and soak in the breathtaking scenery. Additionally, informative signboards share interesting facts about the falls, enhancing the educational aspect of the visit.

I recommend visiting Elephant Falls during the monsoon season when the waterfall is at its most robust and the surrounding greenery is at its peak. However, the falls maintain their charm throughout the year, making it a year-round destination for nature enthusiasts.

In conclusion, Elephant Falls in Shillong is a testament to the unspoiled beauty of Meghalaya. Whether youre a nature lover, a photographer, or simply someone seeking a peaceful escape, this waterfall is a must-visit destination. I left Elephant Falls with a heart full of memories and a deep appreciation for the wonders of the natural world.

name: Kaushal Pujari
review_text:
Elephanta falls one of the most popular tourist destination in shilong Meghalaya. Located at a distance of 12 km from Shilong City .Elephant falls is one of the most visited tourist place.
The view is really awesome and water is very clean .One need to navigate down a steep flight of 150 steps to reach the waterfall.This is a superb place for spending some time amidst the nature.
Highly recommended place when ever you planned a visit to Shilong you must visit this place this will surely refresh your mind and even gives a scenic view of the nature .This is a superb place for spending some time amidst the nature.
Elephant falls can be easily reached via public transport.Elephant falls is one of the natural wonders of Northeast India that you must not miss. Elephant Falls is an excellent place to halt before continuing on your adventure across Meghalaya. It is one of the most frequented falls in the lovely state.Elephant Waterfalls may be visited at any time of the year. The Elephant Falls being a popular spot for photographers. It is said to be one of the best places to go during a Shillong sightseeing. There is no such entry fee to visit this beauty of nature.

name: Salim
review_text:
Elephant Waterfall in Shillong is a natural marvel that captivates visitors with its awe-inspiring beauty. Nestled amidst lush greenery, the cascading waters create a serene and refreshing atmosphere. The journey to the waterfall is an adventure itself, with scenic trails leading to the mesmerizing destination.

Upon reaching the site, the sheer force and grace of Elephant Waterfall are truly captivating. The sound of rushing water and the cool mist in the air create a tranquil ambiance, perfect for nature enthusiasts and those seeking a peaceful escape.

The accessibility and well-maintained surroundings enhance the overall experience. The presence of informational signboards provides interesting insights into the local flora and fauna, enriching the visit with educational value.

Photographers will find ample opportunities to capture the stunning landscape and the majestic waterfall from various angles. The well-maintained viewing points ensure that visitors can appreciate the grandeur of Elephant Waterfall comfortably.

Overall, Elephant Waterfall is a must-visit destination in Shillong, offering a blend of natural beauty and tranquility. Whether youre a nature lover, adventure seeker, or someone looking for a peaceful retreat, this enchanting waterfall is sure to leave a lasting impression.

name: Abhijit Baishya
review_text:
This very well known waterfall is in 3 levels with the 3rd one (at the bottom) being the main attraction.
The area is covered with greenery.
Water level will be low during the winter season and its recommended to visit during monsoon.

One has to climb down to get the 3rd one.
Takes around 5-6mins for adults.
Seniors and elders may avoid this place as there are many stairs and its slippery during and after rain.

Ample parking space is available and entry fees is 100 INR per person.
Recommended for those who like exploring and enjoy being with nature.

name: Tanmoy Mahanta
review_text:
The original Khasi name for the falls is Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, which translates to the three - step waterfall.[3] This name is still used locally. However the modern name is explained by a signboard near the waterfall.[4] The name originated in the British era when the Englishmen spotted a giant rock that looked like an elephant near the fall. This rock was destroyed in the 1897 due to an earthquake.. wiki

Its a wonderful site to behold... three waterfalls in one go... entry fee is 100 per head and thats ok enough as it goes towards the upkeep of the site.
There are stalls at the entrance where you will get food and other items and souvenirs.. but the cost is a bit on the higher side .. even for a bottle of water you have to pay double the MRP.
The site is thronged by visitors almost throughout the year..
You need to go a good number of stairs to see all the three falls but thats worthwhile so far as you are not unfit to climb back the stairs.
The sound of the water is mesmerizing and nature flows in full bounty here.

It is hardly 11kms from the heart of the shillong city and the road too is a site to relish with greeneries all around and pine trees embracing you enroute.

name: Suman Deb
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a magnificent waterfall located in Shillong, Meghalaya, India. It is one of the most popular tourist attractions in the region and offers a breathtaking sight to behold. The falls derive their name from a rock resembling an elephant near the foot of the waterfall. With its mesmerizing beauty and natural charm, Elephant Falls has become a must-visit destination for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts.

The waterfall is formed by three successive falls that cascade down from a height of approximately 100 feet. The first fall is the widest and most powerful, creating a thunderous roar as the water crashes onto the rocks below. The second fall is smaller but equally captivating, while the third fall is hidden amidst dense foliage, adding an element of mystery to the overall experience.

The surrounding landscape of Elephant Falls is nothing short of enchanting. Lush greenery, towering trees, and vibrant flora create a picturesque backdrop against which the falls stand out in all their glory. Visitors can take leisurely walks along well-maintained pathways that lead to different viewpoints, allowing them to capture stunning photographs and immerse themselves in the tranquility of nature.

One of the highlights of visiting Elephant Falls is the opportunity to witness the sheer power and force of nature up close. The thundering sound of water hitting the rocks, combined with the misty spray that fills the air, creates a truly immersive experience for visitors. It is advisable to carry raincoats or umbrellas as the spray from the falls can be quite intense at times.

Apart from its natural beauty, Elephant Falls also holds historical significance. It was originally named Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew by the local Khasi people, which translates to Three Steps Waterfalls. During British colonial rule, it was renamed Elephant Falls due to the presence of a rock formation resembling an elephant near its base.

To enhance visitors experience, the local authorities have developed well-maintained viewpoints, bridges, and staircases that allow easy access to different parts of the falls. There are also seating areas and picnic spots where visitors can relax and enjoy the serene surroundings.

In conclusion, Elephant Falls in Shillong, Meghalaya is a natural wonder that captivates all who visit. Its powerful cascades, lush surroundings, and historical significance make it a must-see attraction for anyone traveling to the region. Whether you are an adventure seeker or simply appreciate the beauty of nature, Elephant Falls is sure to leave a lasting impression.

name: Soul free traveler
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a two-tier waterfall located in Shillong, the capital of Meghalaya, India. It is named after an elephant-shaped rock. The waterfall consists of three levels, each with a different shape and height. The first level is broad and hidden among trees, the second level is narrow and domesticated, and the third level is the tallest and most spectacular, with clear water falling over sharp rocks. Elephant Falls is a popular tourist attraction that offers scenic views, refreshing water, and souvenir shops. It is situated 12 km away from the city center and can be reached by a railed walkway that descends along the face of the waterfall.

name: Nayem Ahmed
review_text:
The first fall of Elephant Falls is an example of a horsetail-punchbowl waterfall. The first fall is very broad and is hidden among trees. The second fall however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes to view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.

The sides of the waterfall are flanked by lush greenery and are rich in ferns.

The first fall at Elephant Falls is an example of a horsetail-punchbowl waterfall. The first fall is very wide and hidden among the trees. But the second fall looks quite tame and unnecessary in winter (and dry months). The third fall is the tallest and most abrupt and looks the most spectacular with crystal clear water cascading over countless sharp rocks.

The waterfall is surrounded by lush greenery and rich in ferns.

name: Nur-E Qadar (Tisha)
review_text:
Elephant Falls of Meghalaya is around 10 kilometres away from the main city of Shillong. This waterfall was named after a rock that resembled as an elephant. The original Khasi name of the waterfall is Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew, which translates to the three - step waterfall. As the name suggests the mountain stream descends through three sucessful falls which can be seen after climbing down flights of stairs.
You can find a number of souvenir shops, small restaurants and a gate with a flight of stairs going down towards the falls.

name: Abhinash Rabha
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a popular tourist destination located in Shillong, Meghalaya, India. The falls are named after an elephant-shaped rock near the waterfall. My journey to Elephant Falls began with a short trek through the lush green forest.

As I reached the falls, I was mesmerized by the beauty of the cascading waterfalls. The sound of the water falling from a height echoed through the valley. I spent some time admiring the falls and taking pictures. The cool breeze and the mist from the waterfall made it a refreshing experience.

The experience at Elephant Falls was unforgettable, and I would highly recommend it to anyone visiting Shillong.

name: Bissmon Thomas
review_text: It is a main waterfall in Shillong. As it is a 3 step falls, it was first named as Ka kshaid pateng khohsiew (3 step falls). When the Britishers came and found the waterfalls, then they renamed it as elephant falls as the left side of the falls was having a rock resembling an elephant. But this rock was destroyed by the earthquake in the year 1897.

name: Someshree Banerjee
review_text: I had the amazing opportunity of visiting the elephant falls of Shillong in the rainy season. The waterfalls were mesmerising. The water flow was great and with the lush greenery that was around the place and the white water made the place look even better. The water was very clean and you get to see three parts of the water fall when you visit this place. My pro tip would be visiting it during the rainy season because that's the time when the water falls is in full bloom.

Must visit on your trip to Meghalaya.

Must carry umbrella and raincoats if you travel to Meghalaya especially during summer and monsoon seasons.
The shops do rent umbrellas at reasonable price. We got it at INR 30 for each.

name: prishi motovlog
review_text:
The name originated in the British era when the Englishmen spotted a giant rock that looked like an elephant near the fall. This rock was destroyed in the 1897 due to an earthquake. To reach the falls, you have to climb 150 steps which would be a little slippery. You will find a few benches along the way for you to sit and relax. Elephant Falls is also referred to as The Three Step Waterfall as you will see three different parts of falls there.

name: Kaushik Mandal
review_text:
Elephant Falls in Shillong is a natural marvel that showcases the raw beauty of cascading water. The falls are named after a rock resembling an elephant, which unfortunately got damaged in an earthquake. Nonetheless, the charm of the falls remains intact. Visitors are captivated by the lush greenery surrounding the falls, creating a picturesque backdrop. The sound of gushing water and the mist in the air create a refreshing and serene atmosphere. Elephant Falls is a popular tourist spot in Shillong, offering a delightful experience for nature enthusiasts and those seeking a peaceful retreat.

name: Martin Bhambhani
review_text:
Elephant Falls in Meghalaya is a stunning natural wonder that is worth a visit. The falls are surrounded by lush greenery and offer a peaceful escape from the hustle and bustle of the city. The cascading waterfalls are a sight to behold, and visitors can enjoy a refreshing swim in the natural pool at the bottom of the falls. However, it is important to be cautious while swimming as the water can be deep and the currents strong. Overall, Elephant Falls is a beautiful destination that should not be missed when visiting Meghalaya.

Edit:

First review written on: 08/07/2018, 07:10 am
A three-tiered waterfall infested by neurotic selfiemaniacs. This is what I can say for this beautiful waterfall. The beauty of Meghalaya is clearly visible in the monsoon in this fall.

name: RAJAT KANTI DEB
review_text:
Elephant falls situated on upper Shillong, east khashi hills.Its a three layers water falls, the first falls is not good, the second falls is better but the third are the most visible,and clean water flowing. You visit here all over the year but the post monsoon is the best time to visit. The total three step water falls are well maintained, good parking area outside the water falls. After all without visiting these water falls your Mahalaya visit is not completed.

name: Sarif Mia
review_text:
My visit to Elephant Fall was an awe-inspiring experience. The natural beauty of this majestic waterfall left me mesmerized. As I approached, the sight of water cascading down the rocks was truly breathtaking. The surrounding lush greenery and the peaceful ambiance added to the enchantment. The crystal-clear water sparkled under the sunlight, creating a picturesque scene. I couldnt resist immersing myself in its refreshing waters, feeling the spray on my skin. The sound of rushing water was both soothing and invigorating. Elephant Fall is a must-visit destination for anyone seeking a slice of natures tranquility and pure beauty.

name: Junayed Ahmed
review_text:
This waterfall at Shillang in Meghalaya, India, is different from other waterfalls in the area and looks really beautiful. The entrance area is also very attractive and clean. When I went to the end of April, the water flow was low, but it didnt take away from its beauty. The stairs leading down to the falls are well-maintained, and its easy for anyone, including older people, to go down and enjoy the stunning view. The whole experience was amazing, and I was impressed by how clean and well-kept the place was. Just keep in mind that the water levels can vary, so its good to check before you go. Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-see destination with its unique beauty and cleanliness.

Visited: April 28,2023

Enjoy the breathtaking beauty of Elephant Falls and appreciate the clean and attractive surroundings it offers.

name: Rajrishi Dubey
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a popular tourist destination located in Shillong, the capital of Meghalaya, India. The falls consist of three tiers, each with its own distinctive beauty and character.

The first tier of the falls is easily accessible and offers a stunning view of the cascading water as it tumbles down a rocky cliff. The second tier can be reached via a short hike and offers a more secluded and peaceful setting, surrounded by dense forest and lush greenery.

The third tier of the falls is the highest and most spectacular, offering a panoramic view of the surrounding landscape. Visitors can hike up to the top of the falls, taking in the stunning views and enjoying the sound of the rushing water.

In addition to the falls themselves, Elephant Falls is also home to a beautiful park, complete with manicured gardens, walking paths, and scenic overlooks. Visitors can relax and take in the beauty of the park, while enjoying a picnic or simply soaking up the tranquil atmosphere.

Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination for anyone seeking natural beauty and tranquility. The falls and surrounding park offer a peaceful and rejuvenating escape from the hustle and bustle of modern life, and a chance to connect with the raw power and majesty of nature.

name: Motaleb Hussain Official
review_text:
Elephant falls is located at a distance of 12 km from the Shillong city, in Upper Shillong, Meghalaya.

It is one the most scenic and famous waterfall in Northeast India. Elephant falls is a popular tourist attraction in Shillong and it is a combination of three (3) rivers...

This is nice place for every one..
There are 3 different falls at this place. First one is easy.
Next two will require you to climb some steps up and down.
Though not slippery still watch out. All 3 waterfalls are of different kind.

name: Disharee Datta Bhattacharya
review_text:
One of the most beautiful falls at Shillong.

Shillong is a place with so many picturesque falls, Elephanta falls is one of them. Its is a three layered falls and the volume of the water is very high as because most of the times Shillong is rainy.

Very well maintained stairs with proper standing and picture taking place.

Highly recommended to come and enjoy this place.

name: Don Talks
review_text:
The Elephant Falls is a popular tourist destination in Shillong, Meghalaya, India. The falls are located about 12 km away from the city center and are easily accessible by road.

The falls are named after an elephant-shaped rock. The falls are a three-tiered waterfall, cascading down from a height of about 70 feet.

To reach the falls, visitors have to descend a series of steps through a lush forested area. The falls are surrounded by beautiful greenery and provide a peaceful and serene atmosphere.

Visitors can spend some time admiring the beauty of the falls and the surrounding nature, take photographs, and even have a picnic in the area. There are also some shops selling souvenirs and local handicrafts near the falls.

Overall, the Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination for tourists visiting Shillong, especially for nature lovers and photographers.

name: PRITAM PANJAL
review_text:
Elephant falls is the most popular and famous waterfalls in Northeast India. It is a cluster of three small waterfalls.
When the British people came and found the waterfall they named it Elephant falls. Because on the left side of the falls there was a Rock resembled the elephant.
But this Rock was destroyed by earthquake in the year 1897.
There is parking place and toilets are clean. There are some local shops on handcrafts item.

name: M N Chikka Muniyappa
review_text:
The Elephant Falls are a two-tier waterfall in Shillong, Meghalaya, India.The mountain stream descends through two successive falls set in dells of fern-covered rocks.
The first fall of Elephant Falls is an example of a horsetail-punchbowl waterfall. The first fall is very broad and is hidden among trees. The second fall however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes to view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.

name: Rajsekhar Choudhury
review_text:
Its one of the most famous waterfalls in Shillong. Located close to the EAC Upper Shillong, its a three tiered waterfalls. Named so by the British, because once there stood a large rock which resembled an elephant. But the rock no longer exists, since it supposedly toppled after the great Assam earthquake of 1897.
Howsoever, the falls is still very beautiful. One needs to climb down about a 100+ steps to reach the bottom of the falls, from where one may see the third and the most beautiful tier.
On full spate, it seems to be a falls of milk, as the water become white as it cascades down.
Swimming in the pool is prohibited.
There are gaurds stationed.
Entry fees is however hefty... Rs. 100/person. Kids below 10years are exempted.

name: Aminul Hoque
review_text: Elephant Falls is a popular tourist destination located in Shillong, India. The falls offer a beautiful and mesmerizing sight as the water cascades down from a height of over 20 meters. The natural beauty of the surrounding forests and rocks adds to the charm of the place. However, the site is not well-maintained, and the stairs leading to the falls are in poor condition, which may pose a challenge to some visitors. Despite this, the sheer beauty of the falls makes it worth the visit, especially for nature lovers and photography enthusiasts. Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-see attraction in Shillong.

name: Anirban Sen
review_text:
I recently had the opportunity to visit Elephant Fall, and I must say that it was an incredible experience. The waterfall is located in a beautiful forest, and the sight of the cascading water is truly mesmerizing. To get the full view of the waterfall, you need to trek down a steep path, which can be a bit challenging, but the effort is definitely worth it.

As I made my way down the path, I could hear the sound of the waterfall getting louder and louder, and the view became more and more stunning with each step. The sight of the powerful water flow was truly breathtaking. Once I reached the base of the waterfall, I felt like I was in a different world altogether. The cool mist from the waterfall felt refreshing on my skin, and I felt a sense of peace and tranquility that is hard to describe in words.

The trek down to the waterfall can be challenging, especially for those who are not used to hiking or trekking. However, the natural beauty of the surroundings and the magnificent view of the waterfall from the bottom make it all worth it. The entire experience is truly unforgettable, and I would highly recommend visiting Elephant Fall to anyone who loves nature and adventure.

In conclusion, Elephant Fall is a must-visit destination for anyone who loves waterfalls.

name: Smith Rakshit
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a popular tourist attraction located in Shillong, India, and its known for its stunning natural beauty and rich history.

Visitors to Elephant Falls are treated to a breathtaking view of a multi-tiered waterfall cascading down the rocks, surrounded by lush greenery and towering trees. The falls are named after a rock formation that resembled an elephant, which unfortunately was destroyed in an earthquake. Nonetheless, the falls remain a popular tourist attraction in the region, and visitors can enjoy the beauty of the waterfall from several viewpoints and walking paths.

Apart from the natural beauty of the falls, visitors can also learn about the history of the area, as Elephant Falls played a significant role in the colonial history of India. The falls were named by the British during the colonial era, and they were a popular picnic spot for British officers and their families.

Visitors can also enjoy various activities around the falls, such as trekking, hiking, and birdwatching, making it a great destination for nature enthusiasts and adventure seekers.

One thing to note is that the falls can get crowded, especially during peak tourist season, so its recommended to visit during off-peak times or arrive early in the day.

Overall, if youre looking for a scenic and historic destination in Shillong, a visit to Elephant Falls is a must. The natural beauty, rich history, and activities make it a great destination for all kinds of travelers.

name: Varun Upase
review_text:
The name was given by the English after they discovered a huge rock that resembled an elephant close to the fall during the British rule. Due to an earthquake in 1897, this rock was damaged.

The first fall of Elephant Falls is an example of a horsetail-punchbowl waterfall. The first fall is very broad and is hidden among trees. The second fall, however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes to view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.
The sides of the waterfall are flanked by lush greenery and are rich in ferns.
A few ducks playing near the waterfall as well as some birds can be seen as well.
To reach the bottom of the falls, there are 125. The steps are well maintained but are a bit slippery in some parts. Due to presence of thick forest area, the temperature at the waterfalls is much cooler than the outside temperature.
Swimming is strictly prohibited in the waterfall.
At the entrance of waterfalls, visitors can also enjoy the traditional outfits and click some photographs with them.
Near the parking lot, there are couple of shops that sell local artifacts.

review_text: Elephant Falls is a stunning waterfall located in the Eastern Himalayas of India. It is located in the state of Meghalaya and is a popular tourist destination due to its beautiful scenery and rich history. The beautiful cascades of the falls create a stunning backdrop for visitors to take in the stunning views. The Elephant Falls is situated near the renowned Shillong Peak and is easily accessible from Shillong, the capital of Meghalaya. The falls are known for their beauty and the fact that there are elephants that can be seen in the area. The falls also provide a great opportunity for bird watching. The area around the falls is known for its lush greenery and lush foliage, making it a great destination for hiking and trekking. Overall, Elephant Falls is a must-visit destination for anyone looking for a beautiful waterfall experience.

name: Arindam Debnath
review_text:
Beautiful waterfalls at the heart of Shillong.

Why the name Elephant Falls?

ORIGINALLY THE KHASI PEOPLE NAMED THIS FALLS KA KSHAID LAI PATENG KHOHSIEW (THREE STEPS WATER FALLS) BECAUSE THE WATER FALLS INTO THREE STEPS.

WHEN THE BRITISHERS CAME AND FOUND THE WATER FALLS THEN THEY RENAMED IT ELEPHANT FALLS BECAUSE ON THE LEFT SIDE OF THE FALLS THERE WAS A ROCK RESEMBLING AN ELEPHANT, BUT THIS ROCK WAS DESTROYED BY THE EARTHQUAKE IN THE YEAR 1897.

name: Bicky Roy
review_text: Elephant falls is a dramatic, picturesque and multi-tiered waterfalls located in Upper Shillong, Meghalaya, India. The name given was due to a elephant-shaped rock which got broken in 1897 due to an earthquake. You can hire a car after reaching Shillong to reach here. The fare is Rs. 100 per head and with an easy walking trail and stairs near the parking area you have to reach the bottom of the falls enjoying the scenic view and the natural formations surrounding the falls.

name: Vikas Singh
review_text:
1. Beautiful tourist spot you must visit while in Shillong

2. Its a three step waterfall

3. Entry fee of 100 rupees per person
(Includes parking)

4. You take the ticket at entrance and then park your vehicle

5. First go down the falls
(Find the reason of naming it as Elephant falls)

6. Go. Down the steps and enjoy the three step water falls
(Its a walk down the stairs - for the people with knee injury)

7. Best view from third step so must go down the step till third

8. Be cautious if water level is high or low
9. Can be slippery near third step fall as it is sometimes wet

10. Other things available
- few shops for munching
- traditional dress shop where you can
get your photo clicked
- few shops to buy some pine  stuff and few local products

11. Nearby there is an amusement park also
2. Its named as elephant falls - however the elephant stone is not there now

Weekday

No wait

name: Bapan Kanti Ojha
review_text: Elephant falls have been named after a rock resembling elephant, which got destroyed in the earthquake of 1897. The Elephant Falls is one of the most popular falls in the entire North East. Located near the Shillong city. The elephant falls consist of three layers of falls at three different points which are accessible to the tourist visiting the falls. People can get closer view of the falls as the barrier is very near to falls one can even touch the flowing water of the falls and enjoy its coolness which refreshes the body and mind.

Elephant Falls:-

name: riggo dirchi
review_text:
I enjoy my holidays with my family at Elephant Falls, although there is not a single elephant in that area. But as per resources Britishers were coined the name Elephant Falls earlier they were ruled India. In that spot one big stone was stuck in the stream that seemed like an elephant. But after the 1950 Earthquake it was rolling away from the core of the stream but the name is still popular. Many people who visit take the photos for memory etc. It was a joyous moment for us to visit the place.

name: sanjoy sinha
review_text:
I visited elephant falls on 5th of October 2022 and it was awesome experience. The security at the front of entrance at the elephant fall take 100 rs per person excluding the driver. After entering throw the gate we park our vehicle on the parking side allotted and we see that there are plenty of shops available for the tourists. There is provision available for tourists to capture their photos in traditional meghalya tribal dresses by hiring traditional dresses of the tribes of Meghalaya. The will check the entry pass bought at the entrance gate before entering the first fall. There are total three falls . We viewed the first waterfall and taken some photos from their. The second fall is situated below the first fall and there are stairs to go down to see the second fall. It is easy to go down and view the waterfall. So we went down and viewed the second waterfall but we cannot make to go down to the third waterfall as it is steep and it is easy to go down the stairs but it is hard to climb up the stairs again . So we ended our journey to the second fall. So we capture some photos at the second fall and viewed the awesome natural experience of the fall. It sounds much like the sound of river flowing in the forest. After that we bought some items from the shop available there and we returned.

name: umesh namram
review_text:
Located 12 km away from Shillong, Elephant Falls is one of the most scenic and famous waterfalls in North East India. Nature lovers come here to spend time amidst tranquility and enjoy the beauty of the surroundings. There are different vantage points from where you can witness the charm of Elephant Falls.

The interesting part of Elephant Falls is a two-tier waterfall cascading down the rocks. These curved falls catch the eye of the visitors and the surrounding green vegetation makes it an ideal picnic spot. Elephant Falls sections into three smaller waterfalls and the combined stream drops down the fern-covered rocks below.

name: Priyam Sen
review_text:
This is one of the sight seeing place in Shillong. There are 3 stages for viewing it and it is a normal one for a view.
The name of Elephant falls is due to the shape of the cave from where the falls run used to look like the mouth of an elephant and hence the name. But due to an earthquake the rock was damaged and hence you will not be able to see it anymore but during monsoon the falls look nice.
I will recommend not to visit this place as there are better falls in Shillong (Wakaba falls) on road to Cherrapunji which is far beautiful.
Here you will also get breakfast but the service is a bit slow.
If u have extra days in hand you can visit this place or else skip it.
We clicked some good pictures and thats all you will get at this place.

Parking: The entry is 50/- per head which includes the parking as well.

name: Golam Mostafa Kamal
review_text:
A very nice place to visit. Natural beauty with waterfall. Entry fees were 100 per bike at no extra charge. Parking is available here. A restaurant is also a small place to shop for bamboo products. Toilet facilities are available free of cost and also drinking water. If you want to spend a good time here it will take 2-3 hours. It is situated near Shillong to Cherapunji road. If you are visiting Cherapunji you will get this place on the way. Outside food is available and you can have it inside the park but use a dustbin to keep the place clean.

name: Karthick M
review_text:
Elephant Falls is a two-tiered waterfall in Shillong, Meghalaya, India. The mountain stream cascades through the rocks surrounding Perani in two continuous cascades.
The Khasi language name of the waterfall is Ka Kshait Lai Pateng Kohsiw. It means three-level waterfall. Local people still use this name. However the current name is mentioned on a notice board near the falls. The big rock near the waterfall looks like an elephant. The British who saw it during the British rule named this waterfall as Elephant Falls. This rock was destroyed during an earthquake in 1987.

name: Bidyanand Hijam
review_text:
The waterfall is the result of a mountain stream that drops over multiple levels, scything through the forested slope. The railed walkways begin at the head of the falls and continue to the bottom, ensuring that you not only see the magnificence of the falls from a close distance but also feel the spray of the cool water and the thunderous sound of the flow. The pool at the bottom of the falls is a tranquil spot where you can wade into the clear water at knee-level and get a nice picture with the giant cascade in the background.

The Khasi name for Elephant Falls is Kshaid-Lai-Pateng, which roughly refers to the three levels over which the water plunges. The name is rather misleading today - the elephant-shaped rock after which it was named by the British was destroyed in an earthquake more than a hundred years ago. At the entrance to Elephant Falls, there is a collection of stalls selling snacks and souvenirs.

name: Siva VSP
review_text: Elephant Falls is undoubtedly one of the main tourist attractions, situated just 12 kilometers away from the state capital. Flanked by the beauty of the frothy water dropping in layers and dense green vegetation, it is a complete sight to behold and can be visited with family on a picnic or with friends for a days' outing. The awesome waterfall was named by the Britishers after a rock at its bottom that appears like an elephant. However, the uncanny resemblance was destroyed by an earthquake in 1897. With three layers of the falls accessible and surrounded in lush greenery, with crystal clear streams of water brushing through its rock, this mesmerizing sight is a complete tourists' paradise. Though the falls can be visited any time of the year, monsoons are the best time to see the falls in their full might and the magical feeling will remain engraved in your mind forever. The three-layered cascading natural view is considered one of the most spectacular waterfalls in India.

name: X Y
review_text: Named after an Elephant like stone at its foot, the Elephant Falls are amongst the most popular falls in the North-East, situated next to Shillong. It is a tourists paradise with three layers of the falls accessible to the layman from different vantage points. The Britishers named this fall so owing to the presence of an elephant-shaped rock on one side of the fall. However, the stone disintegrated and was washed away due to an earthquake in 1897. The breathtaking Elephant falls were referred to as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew by the local Khasi people, which means The Three Step Waterfalls, as these falls consist of three mesmerising falls in succession.

name: Sujit Shanshanwal
review_text:
A popular tourist attraction near Shillong, Elephant falls is a combination of 3 rivers. One of the British officers named it as Elephant falls after they saw a rock which resembled as an elephant. This rock was later destroyed due to earthquake in the year 1897.
In the local Khasi language, the name of the waterfall is Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohshiew whose literal translation from the Khasi language means 'the three-step waterfall'.
The first fall is very broad and is hidden among trees. The second fall however, is quite domesticated and in the winters (and drier months) looks inconsequential. The third fall is the tallest and comes to view suddenly and looks most spectacular with crystal clear water falling over sharp rocks of myriad shapes.

name: Samir Santra
review_text:
The breathtaking Elephant falls were referred to as Ka Kshaid Lai Pateng Khohsiew by the local Khasi people, which means The Three Step Waterfalls, as these falls consist of three mesmerising falls in succession. The first of the three waterfalls are tucked between the dense trees and are very broad. The second waterfall reduces to thin strands of water and is almost negligible in winters due to the receding water levels. The third and the most visible waterfall is the tallest with clear water flowing like a sheet of milk on the dark rocks in the backdrop. Out of the three, the third waterfall tends to strike the visitors as the most impressive. Elephant Falls is a great stopover destination before one heads for further journeys into Meghalaya. Located 12 km away from the capital city of Shillong, it is one of the most visited falls in the beautiful state.
This falls require strong leg for climbing up . There are staircase but they are of boulders .So step height is more than normal.
There are local stalls where you can buy food.
No entry fee.

name: Bishnu Behera
review_text:
Elephant Fall is about 30-40 mins drive from Shillong police bazaar which also depends on the traffic condition. Very nice fall. Lucky that we did not have much rain when we visited so we could enjoy the scenic beauty without much trouble. The early morning rain had made the leaf greens even brighter. About 130-150 steps one way. Fall #2 is not that great. But the first and third are really good falls. Visited on 1st of May, had good volume of water flowing. During summer the water streams might be very thin. Near by shops have tea, coffee, snacks, corn etc. they also provide rented umbrella in case of rain. Would suggest to take it yourself as they charge 100/- rental for umbrella. Corn 40/- per piece. People also take photos here in traditional Khasi Costumes. The cab parking charge was 200/-. No person specific charges. Charges are per vehicle.

Opens from 10 AM
